		&lt;p&gt;
			&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; In order to work around browsers&#039; different rounding behaviours, Foundation will float the last column in a row to the right so the edge aligns. If your row doesn&#039;t have a count that adds up to 12 columns, you can tag the last column with &lt;code&gt;class=&quot;end&quot;&lt;/code&gt; in order to override that behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;
			This won&#039;t work by default in IE8 since it doesn&#039;t support &lt;code&gt;:after&lt;/code&gt; but you can simply add a new class to override this if you run into this problem.&lt;/p&gt;
