		&lt;div class=&quot;row tabs&quot;&gt;
			&lt;div class=&quot;eight columns&quot;&gt;
				&lt;a name=&quot;centered&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
				&lt;h3&gt;
					Centered Columns&lt;/h3&gt;
			&lt;/div&gt;
			&lt;div class=&quot;four columns tabs&quot;&gt;
				&lt;dl class=&quot;tabs pill small&quot;&gt;
					&lt;dd class=&quot;active&quot;&gt;
						&lt;a href=&quot;#centerEx&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/dd&gt;
					&lt;dd&gt;
						&lt;a href=&quot;#centerCode&quot;&gt;Code&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/dd&gt;
				&lt;/dl&gt;
			&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;
			Centered columns are placed in the middle of the row. This does not center their content, but centers the grid element itself. This is a convenient way to make sure a block is centered, even if you change the number of columns it contains. Note: There cannot be any other column blocks in the row for this to work.&lt;/p&gt;
