		&lt;h5&gt;
			Clearing issues with IE8&lt;/h5&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;
			Sometimes there are clearing issues in IE8. If you are seeing these issues, simply uncomment the Block Grid section within your foundation app.js file. If you don&#039;t have those line in your app.js file, copy them below:&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code class=&quot;rainbow&quot; data-language=&quot;javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;selector&quot;&gt;
$&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&#039;.block-grid.two-up&amp;gt;li:nth-child(2n+1)&#039;&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;span class=&quot;function call&quot;&gt;css&lt;/span&gt;({clear: &lt;span class=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&#039;both&#039;&lt;/span&gt;});&lt;span class=&quot;selector&quot;&gt;
$&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&#039;.block-grid.three-up&amp;gt;li:nth-child(3n+1)&#039;&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;span class=&quot;function call&quot;&gt;css&lt;/span&gt;({clear: &lt;span class=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&#039;both&#039;&lt;/span&gt;});&lt;span class=&quot;selector&quot;&gt;
$&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&#039;.block-grid.four-up&amp;gt;li:nth-child(4n+1)&#039;&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;span class=&quot;function call&quot;&gt;css&lt;/span&gt;({clear: &lt;span class=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&#039;both&#039;&lt;/span&gt;});&lt;span class=&quot;selector&quot;&gt;
$&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&#039;.block-grid.five-up&amp;gt;li:nth-child(5n+1)&#039;&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;span class=&quot;function call&quot;&gt;css&lt;/span&gt;({clear: &lt;span class=&quot;string&quot;&gt;&#039;both&#039;&lt;/span&gt;});
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
		&lt;hr /&gt;
		&lt;h5&gt;
			Don&#039;t want mobile?&lt;/h5&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;
			You can either not include it in your custom imports for your Scss project or uncheck it in the customizer. The trick to making this work is to set the &lt;code&gt;max-width&lt;/code&gt; of your &lt;code&gt;.row&lt;/code&gt; so that it doesn&#039;t scale.&lt;/p&gt;
